definitions.definition: A small village and civil parish in West Oxfordshire district, Oxfordshire , England ( OS grid ref SP2720 ) .
A large village and former RAF base in Lyneham and Bradenstoke parish, north Wiltshire , England ( OS grid ref SU0278 ) .
A suburb of Canberra , Australian Capital Territory , Australia . Named after Sir William Lyne .
